    <body><div type="letter">
      <p>St James' Sqre Thursday 4 o'clock</p>
      <p>Dearest W. I have nothing very particular to tell you. H-- arrived between 7 &amp; 8 last night; looking very well &amp; happy. This morning she has been helping me to arrange various matters; my books, papers, &amp;c. For I find that without great order I can hope to do nothing</p>
      <p>whatever. Wheatstone has been with me a long while today, &amp; has taken my translation away with him, after reading it then with me. I hope to receive the proofs of it for correction, by &amp; bye; as I trust Taylor will not reject it. I am now translating a beautiful Italian scientific paper.</p>
      <p>Tonight I take Hester to see Miss Kemble in Norma.--</p>
      <p>I seem likely to lead a</p>
      <p>very quite life I think altogether.-- And I certainly care little about anything but the scientific &amp; the musical.--</p>
    </div></body>
